/// A Video Stream of a Simulator’s Framebuffer.
/// This component can be used to provide a real-time stream of a Simulator’s Framebuffer.
/// This can be connected to additional software via a stream to a File Handle or Fifo.
/// Concurrency model: the <code>writeQueue</code> serializes start/stop, the framebuffer consumer callbacks
/// (<code>didChange</code>/<code>didReceiveDamageRect</code>), and every frame push. The cadence is selected by the
/// <code>cadence</code> strategy: <code>.lazy</code> pushes frames from the damage callback (variable frame rate), while
/// <code>.eager</code> runs a cadence <code>Task</code> that, at a fixed frame rate, dispatches <code>pushFrame</code> back onto
